        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 1:46PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 146 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Waldron, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Subiaco...                        Hon...
Roseville...                      Lucas...
Caulksville...                    Chismville...
Waldron...                        Booneville...
Ratcliff...                       Barber...
Midway in Logan County...         Wilkins...
Driggs...                         Carbon City...
Corley...                         Carolan...
Grayson...                        Magazine...
Paris...                          Elm Park...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
